50:23.220 --> 50:26.857 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The rippling waters stop.

50:26.891 --> 50:30.127 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have been wanting to resolve
not up here,
but down here.

50:30.160 --> 50:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And for the first time, we
resolve the piece
on a single cello note without
accompaniment.

50:36.267 --> 50:39.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The accompaniment has always
been in the middle
register, not noticeable at all.

50:39.904 --> 50:45.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, after this resolution of
the cello, suddenly,
from the heavens, up here, in a
brand-new

50:45.643 --> 50:59.757 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
register, the pianos take over,
those rippling
waters become the topic.

50:59.790 --> 51:02.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we finish with one last
wave.

51:02.426 --> 51:09.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, "The Swan" is
the only
part that he did allow to be
published, but

51:09.400 --> 51:10.367 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the rest of it, he didn't
want...

51:10.401 --> 51:11.368 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ROB KAPILOW: The rest of it is
banished.

51:11.402 --> 51:12.369 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: He wanted it to
go away?

51:12.403 --> 51:13.370 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ROB KAPILOW: He wanted it to go
away.

51:13.404 --> 51:15.572 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
